Defendant Michael Anthony Morgan in court with attorney Christopher Scott Carson.  Defendant Michael Anthony Morgan in custody.  Grant Ian Huebner and Britney Kachwinge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Jurors returned at 9am to resume deliberations.  Jury submitted 2 requests for exhibits (#3,4 and 98-99)  exhibits had been previously stipulated to by counsels to be given to jury upon request.  At 11:20 the jury reached its verdicts.  
At the hour of 11:48am the jury returned and, by their foreperson, (#17)brought in the following  verdicts:
Count 1: (count 1 in 14CM3257):  We, the jury, find the defendant GUILTY of Battery-Domestic Abuse, offense date 8-7-2014;
Count 2: (count 2 in 14CM3257):  We, the jury, find the defendant NOT GUILTY of Criminal Damage to Property;
Count 3: (count 3 in 14CM3257):  We, the jury, find the defendant GUILTY of Disorderly Conduct-Domestic Abuse, offense date 8-7-2014
Count 4: (15CM705):  We, the jury, find the defendant GUILTY of Bail Jumping, offense date 2-26-2015;
Count 5: (count 1 in 15CF4794):  We, the jury, find the defendant GUILTY of Arson, offense date 10-20-2015;
Count 6: (count 2 in 15CF4794):  We, the jury, find the defendant GUILTY of First degree reckless homicide, as to TM;
Count 7: (count 3 in 15CF4794):  We, the jury, find the defendant GUILTY of First degree reckless homicide, as to KL;
Count 8: (count 4 in 15CF4794):  We, the jury, find the defendant GUILTY of Bail jumping, offense date 10-20-2015;
Count 9: (count 5 in 15CF4794):  We, the jury, find the defendant GUILTY of Bail jumping, offense date 10-20-2015
Court polled and discharged the jury.  Verdicts received and filed.  Court granted state's motion for judgment on the verdicts and denied defense motion for judgment not withstanding the verdicts.  Court ordered entry of judgments of conviction.  The court will order a PSI and remand the defendant pending sentencing on 10-27-2016.  Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.
  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 27, 2016 at 08:15 am.
